Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and transport properties of binary liquid mixtures of N-methylacetamide with lactones at temperatures (303.15 to 318.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The values of density (q), viscosity (g) and speed of sound (u) have been measured for binary liquid mixtures  of c-butyrolactone (GBL), d-valerolactone (DVL), and e-caprolactone (ECL) with N-methylacetamide  (NMA) over the whole composition range at T = (303.15 to 318.15) K and atmospheric pressure. From  these data, excess molar volume (VE), deviation in viscosity (Dg), and deviation in isentropic compressibility  (Djs), are calculated. The results are fitted to a Redlich Kister type polynomial equation to derive  binary coefficients and standard deviations.
sKeyword: N-Methylacetamide  Lactones  Excess volume  Viscosity  Isentropic compressibility
